wikipedia_page.main: Henry Watson Wilder (born 3 November 1798 in Marylebone, London; died 2 July 1836 in Yarmouth, Isle Of Wight) was an English first-class cricketer associated with Marylebone Cricket Club (MCC) who was active in the 1810s. He is recorded in one match in 1817, totalling 12 runs with a highest score of 6.
